  "texts": [
    "We take the following steps to construct the training set for each yearly model.",
    "First, from the sample of articles defined in Section 2.2, applying the relevant temporal constraints, we randomly select a balanced set of 20,000 articles along with their patent citation data.",
    "For example, to train the 2020 model, we randomly sample 10,000 articles published between 2006 and 2015 cited in a renewed patent by 2019 (commercial potential) and 10,000 articles not cited in a renewed patent by 2019 (no commercial potential).",
    "Note two key points.",
    "First, we use a fraction of the available data to train each model (20,000 observations each)."
  ],
